title Pls Don't Sue Me Microsoft
author Chanse M
homepage www.puzzlescript.net


(The premise of the game is that you have to ignite all
 Redstone blocks by connecting them to an Igniter block.
 Once ignited, a Redstone block is immobilized. There 
 are also Crates that you can push into Holes to fill 
 them, because what kind of Sokoban game would it be
 without crates?)

(A disaster of a game, that's what kind.)

(Note for later: putting an extra player in a walled-in area next
 to a hole means the player can't move in that direction; can a 
 puzzle work in this framework with one of the directions disabled?)

